## Any other business

Henrik Ingo from Drizzle was present at the meeting and accepted the associated
project status offer on behalf of the project.

There was some query about which email address our SFLC representative should
have subscribed to our board list; a generic role address or a specific
individual. It was agreed that for legal representatives a specific address
made more sense.

Jimmy reported that we'd heard back from Mishi at SFLC confirming that WIPO had
given us a certification of registration of the Debian trademark under the
Madrid Protocol, covering the EU, China, Japan and the UK.


